result.execSummary:
All charges against Demetrey J. Lambouths in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Demetrey J. Lambouths is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:13 AM Attorney Daniel Joseph Tombasco in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Demetrey J. Lambouths in court.  Attorney Alyssah M Foster in court for Demetrey J. Lambouths. Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES: 22CM732/22CM733. Matter is resolved and agreement placed on the record. The State is objecting to any request for expunction.

22CM732: On State's motion, case is dismissed. Bond to be applied to costs and fees in Case 22CM733.

22CM733: Defendant entered a plea of guilty; found guilty by the court. Sentencing arguments heard. Court orders a $300 fine plus costs and DNA surcharge, bond applied from case 22CM732 and remainder due within 90 days, or 12 days KCJ/huber/work crew. Defendant is ordered to submit to a DNA sample; notice given to def. in court. Defendant is ordered to pay restitution in the amount of $49.01; 60 DTP. Court finds the Defendant is eligible for expungement in one year by written request.
